  "texts": [
    "For BERT [19] sequence classification tasks, suggestions are to fine-tune the representation of the special [CLS] token and follow with a single feed-forward layer that classifies it as one of the task labels.",
    "It is common practice to temporarily freeze the language model layers while initially training the feed-forward layers and then unfreeze the language model gradually for additional fine-tuning [33,71].",
    "In all the examples in BERT, there are fewer benefits to training the feed-forward layer alone.",
    "An alternative strategy is to fine-tune a separate small network of the NLP model and select only a few weights of the model to keep.",
    "When using adapters, you can fine-tune only the weights of the adapter."
  ],
